;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:14;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:15;s:112:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse whenever it hits an obstruction such as the driveway or ground.";i:16;s:49:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Closes Then Reopens.";i:17;s:111:"When your garage door keeps opening and closing there are typically several possibilities for this malfunction.";i:18;s:122:"If your garage door reverses when it hits the floor look into these three common causes and try troubleshooting the issue.";i:19;s:72:"For a few months I have been having issues with my electric garage door.";i:20;s:27:"Its started doing 2 things.";i:21;s:101:"1 It goes down to close touches the floor then comes straight back up again so im unable to close it.";i:22;s:122:"2 It closes but it then wont open - when i look inside the error light is on as is the light in the sensor at floor level.";i:23;s:40:"Try to operate the garage door manually.";i:24;s:76:"This helps you determine if the problem is related to the door or the motor.";i:25;s:119:"The garage door can be operated manually by disconnecting the garage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:26;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:27;s:105:"If the garage door opens correctly but fails to close completely there may be one of three common causes.";i:28;s:42:"The close-limit switch may need adjusting.";i:29;s:131:"Your garage door has set-limit switches that instruct the motor when to stop runningboth when it is opening and when it is closing.";i:30;s:193:"If you release the door from the opener using the release cord see image below you should be able to lift the door to half open by hand and the door should stay at that point if you release it.";i:31;s:40:"If not there is a problem with the door.";i:32;s:100:"There could be a bind or drag in the door mechanism or the springs may be damaged or need adjusting.";i:33;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:34;s:49:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse.";i:35;s:101:"The garage door openers all 3 work at opening the door but are very inconsistent in closing the door.";i:36;s:40:"Door close sensors are aligned properly.";i:37;s:47:"The door opens and closes with the wall switch.";i:38;s:159:"I have a garage door opener Stanley D1000 A07 Date 98523 I hit the wall button or remote button and it hums starts to move then stops and reverses itself then.";i:39;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:40;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:41;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:42;s:100:"Check and tighten up the hardware Your garage door will open and close hundreds of times every year.";i:43;s:59:"All those ups and downs will vibrate and loosen some parts.";i:44;s:59:"Check all your bolts and brackets and tighten where needed.";i:45;s:46:"Does the weatherstripping need to be replaced.";i:46;s:60:"There is a rubber seal along the bottom of your garage door.";i:47;s:112:"This component is a safety device that tells the circuit board if the electric motor is actually running or not.";i:48;s:106:"If your doot travels about 30cm then goes back up again then this is the most likely cause of the problem.";i:49;s:33:"When a tilt door starts to close.";i:50;s:43:"My garage door closes most of the way then.";i:51;s:119:"Repeated operation of the garage door as you make the adjustments may cause the opener to overheat and fail to operate.";i:52;s:56:"Wait 15 minutes for the motor to cool before proceeding.";i:53;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:54;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:55;s:99:"As these wires short against the housing the electrical impulse causes the door opener to activate.";i:56;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:57;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:58;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:59;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";}}